

Tim Murphy is a [[Collective Intelligence]] researcher and activist.


=Bio=


"Tim Murphy  - CEO and Founder, Alchemy Films International (http://www.alchemyfilmsinc.com), based in the USA. Tim created Alchemy Films as a global media company to specialize in transformational topics and issues such as the consciousness of business, economics and '''citizen-based governance within whole systems oriented (wisdom) cultures'''.  His latest feature film project is '''MONEY; The Movie, due for release at the end of 2007'''. Tim is a lifelong student and teacher of consciousness transformation systems and methodologies that he is now applying to his media projects. 

He is part of an international network of practitioners working at the leading edge of collective intelligence capacity building and planetary facilitation and is a founder of GaiaSpace (http://www.gaiaspace.org), an innovative online emergence platform, social network and conscious media portal. He is also a certified expert Cisco engineer and trainer (NextGen Internet, fiber optics, routing, switching and convergent technologies like voice and video over the Internet), former Vice President of a successful Internet Service Provider and web hosting company, Managing Director of a strategic consulting company (Integral Development, Strategy & Training, LLC) and lead developer of the Gaiasoft (http://www.gaiasoft.com) associate consultants program. He is currently managing a Whole Systems Performance Mgt. and Change Certification program to be offered through Global Knowledge (www.globalknowledge.com), the largest technology and project management training organization in the world.

The network involved in curriculum development of the program includes Gaiasoft, Generon, Society for Organizational Learning, MIT Media Lab, Resilience Corp., McKinsey, Richard Barrett and Associates, EnlightenNext/WIE Magazine, The Alliance for New Humanity, The Conscious Business Institute, The Center for Human Emergence, Newfield Network, Accomplishment Coaching and an expanding list of complexity, system and sustainable transformation practitioners globally."
(source: email correspondence with the author)



